          </p>

          <h3>Unrecognized Universities</h3>

          <p>
            Accreditation in your home country does not guarantee recognition in the UAE. A university accredited by India's UGC or Pakistan's HEC may not be on <a href="/resources/mohesr-equivalency/">MOHESR's recognized list</a>. If MOHRE flags your university, you may need to go through the MOHESR equivalency process (now called "Certificate of Recognition") before the work permit can proceed.
          </p>

          <h3>Distance Learning and Online Degrees</h3>

          <p>
            MOHESR's 2023 policy permits some distance learning degrees if the institution is accredited. However, online degrees in medicine, engineering, and law are categorically rejected. If your degree was earned through distance learning, check with MOHESR before assuming it will be accepted.
          </p>

          <h3>Name Discrepancies</h3>

          <p>
            Even minor transliteration differences between your passport name and your degree certificate trigger rejection. Mohammad on the passport but Mohammed on the degree? That is enough.
          </p>

          <p>
            The translator can add a clarifying note, but prevention is better: when issuing new academic documents, ensure the name spelling matches your passport exactly.
          </p>

